folder: Stockholm Street & Bushwick Avenue, Brooklyn, NY
text:
A rear view of buildings on Stockholk Street, south side, between Bushwick and Evergreen Aves. (Andrew Stockholw sold these sites to William
Coil in 1855).
1897.
Eugene L Armbruster Collectien.

folder: Bushwick Avenue & Kosciusko Street, Brooklyn, NY

Bushwick Ave at the northwest corner of Kosciusko Street, showing Public School no. 68

Board of Education of the City of New York early 1930's

folder: Bushwick Avenue & Kosciusko Street, Brooklyn, NY
text:
833-853 Bushwick Ave, north side, east from Kosciusko Street.  The view shows in the background the steeple of the South Bushwick Reformed Church.  At the right foreground is Kosciusko Street.

Sept. 9th, 1932
